'''Julián Alvarez'''{{efn|name="Álvarez is Alvarez"|group=lower-greek|His surname can also be found as '''Álvarez''' in football statistics databases, football news, and other relative media outlets, and his name as '''Julian'''.}} ({{IPA|es|xuˈljan ˈalbaɾeθ}}; born 31 January 2000) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{Spanish football updater|Atlético Madrid}} club [[Atlético Madrid]] and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

Alvarez began his football career in his native Argentina, where he was an academy graduate of [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]], making his first-team debut for the club in 2018. There, he spent four seasons and won the [[Copa Argentina]], [[2018 Copa Libertadores]] and the [[Argentine Primera División]] in 2021, finishing as the competition's top scorer. He was named the [[South American Footballer of the Year]] in 2021. He was signed by [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in 2022, winning a treble of the [[Premier League]], [[FA Cup]] and [[UEFA Champions League]] in his [[2022–23 Manchester City F.C. season|debut campaign]], before leaving for Atlético Madrid in 2024 in a club-record departure deal worth up to €95 million.

Alvarez previously represented Argentina at various youth levels, competing at the [[2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] and [[2020 CONMEBOL Pre-Olympic Tournament]]. He made his senior international debut in 2021, and played for the squads that won the [[2021 Copa América]], the [[2022 Finalissima]], the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], and the [[2024 Copa América]].

==Club career==
===River Plate===
[[File:Palestino - River Plate 20190424 31.jpg|left|thumb|226x226px|Alvarez training with [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] in 2019]]
Alvarez joined [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] from Atlético Calchín in 2016, notably participating in the [[Generation Adidas Cup]] with the club's youth teams.<ref name="Soccerway">{{cite news |title=Argentina - J. Álvarez |website=Soccerway |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/julian-alvarez/551778/ |access-date=31 October 2018 |archive-date=19 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211119155955/https://int.soccerway.com/players/julian-alvarez/551778/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="GOAL1">{{cite news |title=Julian Alvarez: The ex-Real Madrid kid spearheading River Plate's Libertadores quest |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/julian-alvarez-the-ex-real-madrid-kid-spearheading-river/onxx4gbgla9i1lqtl48adnfbh |access-date=18 December 2020 |website=Goal.com |date=17 December 2020 |archive-date=18 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201218030926/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/julian-alvarez-the-ex-real-madrid-kid-spearheading-river/onxx4gbgla9i1lqtl48adnfbh |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="River Plate">{{cite news |title=Álvarez: Llego al gol por gconsecuencia del juego |url=http://www.cariverplate.com.ar/lvarez-llego-al-gol-por-consecuencia-del-juego |access-date=31 October 2018 |work=River Plate |archive-date=20 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190320102504/http://www.cariverplate.com.ar/lvarez-llego-al-gol-por-consecuencia-del-juego |url-status=live}}</ref> Prior to signing for River, Alvarez had trials with [[Boca Juniors]] and [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]; scoring twice in five games for the latter in a youth tournament.<ref name="GOAL1"/><ref name="Clarín 1">{{cite news |title=La historia del pibe al que Gallardo le dio la 9 de River para la Copa Libertadores (The story of the kid to whom Gallardo gave River's 9 for the Copa Libertadores) |url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/futbol/river-plate/historia-pibe-gallardo-dio-river-copa-libertadores_0_SyGAoAdS7.html |access-date=31 October 2018 |work=Clarín |date=9 August 2018 |archive-date=31 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331104023/https://www.clarin.com/deportes/futbol/river-plate/historia-pibe-gallardo-dio-river-copa-libertadores_0_SyGAoAdS7.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="La Nación">{{cite news |title=Se probó en Real Madrid, estuvo en el Mundial y el sábado debutaría en River |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/2185182-quien-es-julian-alvarez-river-inferiores |access-date=31 October 2018 |work=La Nación |date=25 October 2018 |archive-date=15 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181115225043/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/2185182-quien-es-julian-alvarez-river-inferiores |url-status=live}}</ref> He was unable to join Real due to age restrictions.<ref name="GOAL1"/> Alvarez was moved into River Plate's senior squad under manager [[Marcelo Gallardo]] during the [[2018–19 Argentine Primera División|2018–19]] season, with his professional debut arriving on 27 October 2018 during a [[Argentine Primera División|Primera División]] fixture with [[Aldosivi]]; he was subbed on for [[Rodrigo Mora (footballer, born 1987)|Rodrigo Mora]] with 26 minutes remaining of a 1–0 victory.<ref name="Soccerway"/><ref name="BDFA">{{cite news |title=Ficha Estadistica de Julian Alvarez |url=http://www.bdfa.com.ar/jugador.asp?codigo=115018 |access-date=31 October 2018 |work=BDFA |archive-date=5 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220605214104/https://www.bdfa.com.ar/jugador.asp?codigo=115018 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="TyC Sports">{{cite news |title=Julián Álvarez, el 9 que hizo su debut en River |url=https://www.tycsports.com/nota/superliga/2018/10/27/julian-alvarez-el-9-que-hizo-su-debut-en-river.html |access-date=31 October 2018 |work=TyC Sports |date=27 October 2018 |archive-date=1 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181101015432/https://www.tycsports.com/nota/superliga/2018/10/27/julian-alvarez-el-9-que-hizo-su-debut-en-river.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

Alvarez appeared late on during the second leg of the [[2018 Copa Libertadores finals]], with River beating rivals Boca Juniors.<ref name="Soccerway"/> Alvarez scored the first goal of his senior career on 17 March 2019, netting in a 3–0 league win over [[Club Atlético Independiente|Independiente]].<ref name="Soccerway"/> During the succeeding December, he scored in the [[2019 Copa Argentina Final|2019 Copa Argentina final]] against [[Central Córdoba de Santiago del Estero|Central Córdoba]] as River won 3–0 to secure the trophy. In 2020, Alvarez netted five goals in six [[Copa Libertadores]] group stage encounters.{{Citation needed|date=January 2026}}

On 25 May 2022, Alvarez scored six goals for River Plate in an 8–1 win over [[Club Alianza Lima|Alianza Lima]] in the [[2022 Copa Libertadores|Copa Libertadores]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://mscfootball.com/2022/05/future-manchester-city-player-julian-alvarez-scores-six-goals-for-river-plate-in-8-1-win/ |title=Future Manchester City Player Julian Alvarez Scores Six Goals for River Plate in 8-1 Win |date=26 May 2022 |access-date=26 May 2022 |archive-date=26 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220526052540/https://mscfootball.com/2022/05/future-manchester-city-player-julian-alvarez-scores-six-goals-for-river-plate-in-8-1-win/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

===Manchester City===

==== 2022–23: Debut season and continental treble ====
On 31 January 2022, his 22nd birthday, it was confirmed that Alvarez had signed for [[Premier League]] champions [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] on a five-and-a-half-year contract for a transfer fee in the region of £14 million,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Manchester City clinch signing of River Plate's Julián Álvarez for £14m |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/jan/31/manchester-city-sign-julian-alvarez-river-plate-14m |work=The Guardian |date=31 January 2022 |accessdate=31 December 2023}}</ref> and an agreement that the player would remain at River Plate on loan until July.<ref>{{cite news |title=City sign Julian Alvarez from River Plate |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-complete-signing-of-julian-alvarez-63779231 |access-date=31 January 2022 |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=31 January 2022 |archive-date=23 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221023090319/https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-complete-signing-of-julian-alvarez-63779231 |url-status=live}}</ref>[[File:Julián Álvarez (footballer) 2023.jpg|thumb|226x226px|Alvarez with Manchester City in 2023]]
Alvarez made his competitive debut on 30 July, where City lost 3–1 to [[Liverpool F.C.–Manchester City F.C. rivalry|rivals]] [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in the [[2022 FA Community Shield]], scoring his team's only goal in the process.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Hafez |first=Shamoon |date=29 July 2022 |title=Community Shield: Liverpool 3-1 Man City - Darwin Nunez seals victory |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/live/football/62275194 |access-date=30 July 2022}}{{Dead link|date=April 2023 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On 7 August, Alvarez made his Premier League debut after coming on as a substitute for [[Erling Haaland]] in a 2–0 away win over [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].<ref>{{cite news |last=McNulty |first=Phil |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62366384 |title=West Ham 0-2 Man City: Erling Haaland scores twice as Man City turn on style |publisher=BBC Sport |date=7 August 2022 |access-date=7 August 2022 |archive-date=7 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220807020635/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62366384 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 31 August, Alvarez scored his first two Premier League goals in a 6–0 win against [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] at the [[City of Manchester Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62655348 |title=Man City 6-0 Nottingham Forest: Erling Haaland scores another hat-trick in easy victory |website=BBC Sport |date=31 August 2022 |access-date=31 August 2022 |archive-date=1 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221101161811/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62655348 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 5 October, he scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a 5–0 win over [[F.C. Copenhagen|Copenhagen]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/manchester-city-julian-alvarez-pep-guardiola-norwegian-erling-haaland-b2196822.html |title=Pep Guardiola talks up 'weapon' Julian Alvarez after latest Man City goal |work=The Independent |date=6 October 2022 |access-date=20 May 2023 |archive-date=20 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230520150800/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/manchester-city-julian-alvarez-pep-guardiola-norwegian-erling-haaland-b2196822.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 17 May 2023, Alvarez scored the last goal in a 4–0 win over [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] semi-final second leg, which cemented his club's qualification to the final.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-real-madrid-champions-league-semifinal-second-leg-63819943 |title=Super City secure UCL final spot with stunning win over Real Madrid |publisher=Manchester City |date=17 May 2023 |access-date=20 May 2023 |archive-date=20 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230520150800/https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-real-madrid-champions-league-semifinal-second-leg-63819943 |url-status=live}}</ref> Four days later, he scored the only goal in a 1–0 victory over [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] to win his first Premier League title, and third in a row for his club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/may/21/manchester-city-chelsea-premier-league-match-report |title=Manchester City cap title triumph with win over Chelsea thanks to Álvarez |work=The Guardian |date=21 May 2023 |access-date=21 May 2023 |archive-date=21 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230521190229/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/may/21/manchester-city-chelsea-premier-league-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref> On 10 June, he won the [[2023 UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]] with his club, despite being a non-playing substitute, to become among the players who won the FIFA World Cup and Champions League in the same season, in addition to achieving both the latter and the Copa Libertadores. With this, he also became the first ever player in football history to win the World Cup and a continental treble in the same season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://mundoalbiceleste.com/2023/06/10/julian-alvarez-and-maximo-perrone-win-champions-league-with-manchester-city/ |title=Julián Álvarez and Máximo Perrone win Champions League with Manchester City |publisher=Mundo Albiceleste |date=10 June 2023 |access-date=10 June 2023 |archive-date=10 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230610222357/https://mundoalbiceleste.com/2023/06/10/julian-alvarez-and-maximo-perrone-win-champions-league-with-manchester-city/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2023–24: Starting eleven breakthrough and departure====
On 19 August, Alvarez netted the lone goal in a 1–0 victory over [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 September 2023 |title=Julian Alvarez's first-half goal enough for Man City to beat Newcastle in EPL |url=https://apnews.com/article/manchester-city-newcastle-premier-league-alvarez-cc9c10fa5cdce9a1327b5149c81f0182 |access-date=8 October 2023 |website=[[AP News]] |language=en |archive-date=8 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231008182729/https://apnews.com/article/manchester-city-newcastle-premier-league-alvarez-cc9c10fa5cdce9a1327b5149c81f0182 |url-status=live}}</ref> Following the injuries of [[Bernardo Silva]] and [[Kevin De Bruyne]], Alvarez began featuring more regularly in the starting eleven, registering four goal contributions in his next Premier League matches, including two assists in a 3–1 away win over West Ham United on 16 September.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/west-ham-united-v-city-match-report-63830469 |title=City fight back to win Hammers thriller and maintain perfect start |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=16 September 2023 |access-date=8 October 2023 |archive-date=5 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231005090353/https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/west-ham-united-v-city-match-report-63830469 |url-status=live}}</ref> Three days later, he scored a brace in City's 3–1 home win over [[Red Star Belgrade]] in the UEFA Champions League.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Marrett |first=Adam |date=21 September 2023 |title=Matheus Nunes makes an immediate impact in first start for City. |url=https://esteemedkompany.com/2023/09/21/matheus-nunes-makes-an-immediate-impact-in-first-start-for-manchester-city/ |access-date=23 September 2023 |website=Esteemed Kompany |language=en |archive-date=7 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231007201435/https://esteemedkompany.com/2023/09/21/matheus-nunes-makes-an-immediate-impact-in-first-start-for-manchester-city/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Alvarez finished in 7th place in the [[2023 Ballon d'Or]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=October 31, 2023 |title=Ballon d'Or 2023 official rankings: Lionel Messi beats Erling Haaland and Kylian Mbappe to claim eighth Golden Ball |url=https://www.goal.com/en-ng/lists/ballon-dor-2023-official-rankings/blt67b37a84a3acec81 |access-date=4 November 2023 |magazine=Goal |archive-date=31 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231031184542/https://www.goal.com/en-ng/lists/ballon-dor-2023-official-rankings/blt67b37a84a3acec81 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 22 December, Manchester City defeated [[Fluminense FC|Fluminense]] 4–0 in the [[2023 FIFA Club World Cup final]] as Alvarez scored a brace and provided an assist to claim his first [[FIFA Club World Cup|Club World Cup]] title and finish the tournament as top scorer; with his first goal being the fastest in the competition's history at 40 seconds. On 4 May 2024, Alvarez made his 100th appearance for City, marking it with a late goal in a 5–1 league win over [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/julian-alvarez-100-city-appearances-63850445 |title=Alvarez reaches 100 City appearances |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=4 May 2024 |access-date=4 May 2024}}</ref>

===Atlético Madrid===
[[File:FC Salzburg vs. Atletico Madrid (2025-01-29 UEFA Championsleague) 74.jpg|thumb|Alvarez (right) playing for Atlético Madrid against [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] in 2025]]
On 12 August 2024, [[La Liga]] club [[Atlético Madrid]] confirmed the signing of Alvarez on a six-year deal reportedly worth up to €95 million (£81.8 million), which became a club-record departure for City.<ref>{{cite news |date=12 August 2024 |title=Welcome, Julián Alvarez! |url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/welcome-julian-alvarez |access-date=12 August 2024 |publisher=[[Atlético Madrid]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Ornstein |first=David |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5681745/2024/08/06/julian-alvarez-atletico-madrid-transfer/ |title=Atletico Madrid agree €95m deal with Manchester City for Julian Alvarez |publisher=The Athletic |date=6 August 2024 |access-date=12 August 2024}}</ref> On 19 August, he made his debut for the club, as a substitute, in a 2–2 draw against [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] in the league.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 August 2024 |title=Villarreal hold Atletico Madrid to a draw in first game of season |url=https://www.espn.in/football/report/_/gameId/704669 |access-date=23 August 2024}}</ref> On 15 September, Alvarez scored his first goal for the club in the 90th minute of a 3–0 victory over [[Valencia FC|Valencia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/704705 |title=Atlético beat struggling Valencia as Gallagher makes LaLiga history |publisher=ESPN |date=16 September 2024 }}</ref> On 12 March 2025, Atlético Madrid and Real Madrid went to penalties after tying 2–2 on aggregate in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League#Round of 16|round of 16]] of the UEFA Champions League. Alvarez took Atlético's second penalty, but slipped as he took it yet appeared to successfully convert it, however through the [[video assistant referee]] it was determined that Alvarez had slightly touched the ball with his standing foot before striking it, causing the goal to be disallowed for double-touching the ball. Real Madrid would go on to win the penalty shoot-out 4–2 and advance to the next round. A day later, [[UEFA]] released a statement explaining that the decision to disallow Alvarez's penalty was the correct one, but that they would enter discussions with [[FIFA]] and [[International Football Association Board|IFAB]] to determine whether the rule should be reviewed in cases in which the double touch is clearly unintentional.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Atleti vs Real Madrid |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2044778--atleti-vs-real-madrid/timeline/ |access-date=16 March 2025 |website= |publisher=[[UEFA]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=13 March 2025 |title=UEFA statement on VAR decision at Atlético de Madrid vs Real Madrid match |url=https://www.uefa.com/news-media/news/0297-1d449595df1f-e4e8a42fabeb-1000--uefa-statement-on-var-decision-at-atletico-de-madrid-vs-re/ |access-date=16 March 2025 |website= |publisher=UEFA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=13 March 2025 |title=UEFA to discuss with FIFA, IFAB rule that disallowed Alvarez penalty |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/uefa-discuss-with-fifa-ifab-rule-that-caused-alvarez-penalty-be-disallowed-2025-03-13/ |access-date=16 March 2025 |work= |publisher=[[Reuters]]}}</ref>

On 24 September 2025, he scored a winning hat-trick in a 3–2 victory against [[Rayo Vallecano]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Après un début de saison décevant en Liga, l'Atlético de Madrid se lance contre le Rayo Vallecano grâce à un triplé de Julian Alvarez |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Apres-un-debut-de-saison-catastrophique-en-liga-l-atletico-de-madrid-se-relance-contre-le-rayo-vallecano-grace-a-un-triple-de-julian-alvarez/1596383 |access-date=25 September 2025 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> On 29 April 2026, he converted a penalty in a 1–1 draw against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League semi-final]] first leg, reaching a club-record ten goals in a single campaign,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/2026-04-29-alvarez-is-the-first-player-in-atleticos-history-to-score-10-goals-in-a-champions-league/ |title=Julian Alvarez is the first player in Atletico’s history to score 10 goals in a Champions League season |publisher=Tribuna.com |date=29 April 2026 }}</ref> and becoming the fastest South American player to reach 25 goals in the competition, doing so in 41 matches and surpassing the previous record held by [[Lionel Messi]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Narayan |first=Aaditya |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/48633388/uefa-champions-league-stats-alvarez-surpasses-messi-enrique-moves-guardiola-kvaratskhelia-psg-record |title=UCL stats: Álvarez surpasses Messi, Enrique moves past Guardiola; Kvaratskhelia's PSG record |publisher=ESPN |date=30 April 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
=== 2018–2020: Youth career ===
In 2018, Alvarez was selected by the [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina U-20s]] to train against the [[Argentina national football team|senior team]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref name="Mundod Lavoz">{{cite news |title=Es cordobés, hace siete años se fotografió con Messi y hoy entrenan juntos |url=http://mundod.lavoz.com.ar/futbol/es-cordobes-hace-siete-anos-se-fotografio-con-messi-y-hoy-entrenan-juntos |accessdate=31 October 2018 |work=Mundod Lavoz |date=21 March 2018 |archive-date=31 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031214908/http://mundod.lavoz.com.ar/futbol/es-cordobes-hace-siete-anos-se-fotografio-con-messi-y-hoy-entrenan-juntos |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Clarín 2">{{cite news |title=De 18 años - Julián Alvarez, el pibe argentino que jugó en Real Madrid y hoy es sparring de Lionel Messi |url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/mundial-2018/julian-alvarez-pibe-argentino-jugo-real-madrid-hoy-sparring-lionel-messi_0_HyCH9t2kX.html |accessdate=31 October 2018 |work=Clarín |date=1 June 2018 |archive-date=26 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220226223503/https://www.clarin.com/deportes/mundial-2018/julian-alvarez-pibe-argentino-jugo-real-madrid-hoy-sparring-lionel-messi_0_HyCH9t2kX.html |url-status=live}}</ref> In December, Alvarez was picked for the [[2019 South American U-20 Championship]].<ref name="AFA 1">{{cite news |title=Convocados para el Sudamericano Sub 20 |url=http://www.afa.com.ar/11288/convocados-para-el-sudamericano-sub-20 |accessdate=2 January 2019 |work=AFA |date=22 December 2018 |archive-date=2 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102050811/http://www.afa.com.ar/11288/convocados-para-el-sudamericano-sub-20 |url-status=dead}}</ref> In preparation for the [[2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup]], he scored the second goal against [[Saudi Arabia national under-20 football team|Saudi Arabia]] in what was a 5–0 victory, during a friendly tournament played in Spain. After that, he received a call-up from Fernando Batista for the [[2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in May 2019.<ref name="AFA 2">{{cite news |title=Lista de convocados para el Mundial |url=http://www.afa.com.ar/12140/lista-de-convocados-para-el-mundial |accessdate=4 May 2019 |work=AFA |archive-date=4 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190504144225/http://www.afa.com.ar/12140/lista-de-convocados-para-el-mundial |url-status=dead}}</ref> Four matches and one goal, versus [[South Africa national under-20 soccer team|South Africa]], arrived for him in Poland.<ref name="Soccerway"/> Batista subsequently called Alvarez up for the [[Argentina national under-23 football team|Olympic Team]] in the succeeding September, which preceded his selection for the [[2020 CONMEBOL Pre-Olympic Tournament]]; which Argentina won, with Alvarez scoring once (versus [[Venezuela national under-23 football team|Venezuela]]) in seven matches.<ref name="Soccerway"/><ref name="AFA 3">{{cite news |title=La Selección Sub 23 jugará ante Bolivia desde las 19, en el estadio de Banfield |url=https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/la-seleccion-sub-23-enfrentara-a-bolivia-desde-las-19-en-el-estadio-de-banfield |accessdate=4 September 2019 |work=AFA |date=3 September 2019 |archive-date=19 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201119141250/https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/la-seleccion-sub-23-enfrentara-a-bolivia-desde-las-19-en-el-estadio-de-banfield |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== 2021–present: Senior debut, Copa América and World Cup triumphs ===
[[File:Arg vs mex julianalvarez ochoa y messi (cropped).jpg|thumb|194x194px|Alvarez playing for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]]]
Alvarez made his debut for the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina senior team]] on 3 June 2021, in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Chile national football team|Chile]] as a 62nd-minute substitute for [[Ángel Di María]].<ref>{{cite web |publisher=[[ESPN]] |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=561064 |title=Argentina v Chile game report |date=3 June 2021 |access-date=7 June 2021 |archive-date=7 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210607142541/https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=561064 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 29 March 2022, he scored his first international goal in a 1–1 draw against [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=How many goals has Julian Alvarez scored for Argentina? |url=https://www.elfutbolero.us/conmebol/How-many-goals-has-Julian-Alvarez-scored-for-Argentina-20220329-0024.html |date=29 March 2022 |access-date=13 April 2022 |website=El Futbolero |archive-date=7 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220607203456/https://www.elfutbolero.us/conmebol/How-many-goals-has-Julian-Alvarez-scored-for-Argentina-20220329-0024.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 11 November 2022, Alvarez was included in [[Lionel Scaloni]]'s 26-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tycsports.com/seleccion-argentina/lista-seleccion-argentina-mundial-de-qatar-2022-id476596.html |title=Lista de la Selección Argentina para el Mundial de Qatar 2022 |date=11 November 2022 |access-date=11 November 2022 |language=es |publisher=[[TyC Sports]] |archive-date=11 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221111151332/https://www.tycsports.com/seleccion-argentina/lista-seleccion-argentina-mundial-de-qatar-2022-id476596.html |url-status=live}}</ref> On 30 November, he scored his first World Cup goal in a 2–0 win in the last group stage match against [[Poland national football team|Poland]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63725317 |title=World Cup 2022: Poland 0-2 Argentina - South Americans top group after dramatic night |publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 November 2022 |access-date=30 November 2022 |archive-date=29 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221129183836/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63725317 |url-status=live}}</ref> He followed with a second World Cup goal on 3 December, when he scored in Argentina's 2–1 [[2022 FIFA World Cup#Round of 16|win against Australia]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 December 2022 |title=Argentina 2-1 Australia |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/match-centre/match/17/255711/285073/400128131 |access-date=3 December 2022 |website=FIFA |archive-date=2 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221202162235/https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/match-centre/match/17/255711/285073/400128131 |url-status=live}}</ref> He continued his scoring streak by adding two more goals in Argentina's 3–0 win against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] in the semi-finals, becoming the youngest player since [[Pelé]] in [[1958 FIFA World Cup|1958]] to score two goals in a World Cup semi-final at 22 years, 316 days old.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.foxsports.com/watch/play-61645e7f200004b |title=Argentina vs. Croatia Highlights – 2022 FIFA World Cup |work=Fox Sports |date=13 December 2022 |access-date=13 December 2022 |archive-date=13 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221213211848/https://www.foxsports.com/watch/play-61645e7f200004b?cmpid=google-one-box |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Julián Álvarez, el doblete más joven desde Pelé |url=https://www.infobae.com/america/agencias/2022/12/13/julian-alvarez-el-doblete-mas-joven-desde-pele/ |access-date=22 January 2023 |website=Infobae |date=13 December 2022 |language=es-ES |archive-date=22 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230122184159/https://www.infobae.com/america/agencias/2022/12/13/julian-alvarez-el-doblete-mas-joven-desde-pele/ |url-status=live}}</ref> On 18 December 2022, he was involved in Argentina's second goal as his team defeated [[France national football team|France]] 4–2 on penalties after the match ended 3–3 in extra-time of the final to win the World Cup.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/world-cup-qatar-2022-tournament-review-argentina-messi-mbappe-morocco-croatia-japan |title=A ground-breaking World Cup with a fairy tale ending |publisher=[[FIFA]] |accessdate=18 December 2022 |archive-date=18 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221218220558/https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/world-cup-qatar-2022-tournament-review-argentina-messi-mbappe-morocco-croatia-japan |url-status=live}}</ref>

Alvarez competed for [[Argentina at the 2024 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web |title=ALVAREZ Julian |url=https://olympics.com/en/paris-2024/athlete/julian-alvarez_1930235 |work=[[Paris 2024 Olympics]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241127172628/https://olympics.com/en/paris-2024/athlete/julian-alvarez_1930235 |archive-date=27 November 2024}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Alvarez is regarded as a versatile forward capable of playing across the front line.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Odey |first=Emmanuel |date=27 June 2023 |title=Julian Alvarez has had a Surreal First Year at Manchester City |url=https://bitterandblue.sbnation.com/2023/6/27/23774736/julian-alvarez-has-had-a-surreal-first-year-at-manchester-city |access-date=26 October 2023 |website=Bitter and Blue |language=en |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026081003/https://bitterandblue.sbnation.com/2023/6/27/23774736/julian-alvarez-has-had-a-surreal-first-year-at-manchester-city |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web |date=1 April 2023 |title=Alvarez revels to underline status as world's best second-choice striker |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/julian-alvarez-man-city-premier-league-b2312353.html |access-date=26 October 2023 |website=The Independent |language=en |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026081003/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/julian-alvarez-man-city-premier-league-b2312353.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web |date=18 January 2022 |title=Player Analysis: Why is Man United target Julian Alvarez so highly rated? |url=https://thefootballfaithful.com/player-analysis-why-is-man-united-target-julian-alvarez-so-highly-rated/ |access-date=26 October 2023 |website=The Football Faithful {{!}} Football News {{!}} Premier League News {{!}} Football Opinions {{!}} Football Analysis {{!}} Football Betting Tips {{!}} Football Transfers {{!}} The Football Faithful |language=en-GB |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026081005/https://thefootballfaithful.com/player-analysis-why-is-man-united-target-julian-alvarez-so-highly-rated/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He has been noted for his pace, closing ability and control, and scoring ability from difficult positions. Commentators have also noted his link-up play, passing ability, vision, and movement such as quick passes and one-touch football.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Lee |first=Sam |title=Julian Alvarez: Manchester City's 'unique' player |language=en |work=The Athletic |date=3 May 2023 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4473650/2023/05/01/julian-alvarez-manchester-city/ |access-date=26 October 2023 |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026081005/https://theathletic.com/4473650/2023/05/01/julian-alvarez-manchester-city/ |url-status=live}}</ref>  He also is recognized for his work rate on and off the ball, while also contributing to pressing opponents.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":3">{{Cite news |last=Cox |first=Michael |title=Julian Alvarez is Argentina's No 9 but increasingly a Man City No 8 |work=The New York Times |date=18 May 2023 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4520275/2023/05/15/pep-guardiolas-latest-positional-reinvention-julian-alvarez-as-a-no-8/ |access-date=26 October 2023 |language=en |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026081005/https://theathletic.com/4520275/2023/05/15/pep-guardiolas-latest-positional-reinvention-julian-alvarez-as-a-no-8/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite news |last=Lee |first=Sam |title=Of course Man City want Haaland to play... but Alvarez really is a dream fit |work=The New York Times |date=2 April 2023 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4370939/2023/04/02/julian-alvarez-manchester-city-haaland/ |access-date=26 October 2023 |language=en |archive-date=23 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231223140932/https://theathletic.com/4370939/2023/04/02/julian-alvarez-manchester-city-haaland/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Alvarez has also been described as an effective [[Free kick (association football)|free-kick]] taker, scoring several free-kicks during his career in Europe.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Horncastle |first=James |date=9 April 2026 |title=Julian Alvarez’s Atletico free kick goal in Barcelona was a reminder that a dying art is not yet dead |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/7181894/2026/04/09/julian-alvarez-atletico-madrid-free-kick/ |access-date=9 April 2026 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

Alvarez is known for his first touch being composed and intentional, with his ability of both killing a ball dead or kicking it away from defenders in his path.<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=Desmond |first=Rhys |date=1 February 2022 |title=Why Julian Alvarez is perfect for Manchester City |url=https://themastermindsite.com/2022/02/01/why-julian-alvarez-is-perfect-for-manchester-city/ |access-date=26 October 2023 |website=TheMastermindSite |language=en |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026082507/https://themastermindsite.com/2022/02/01/why-julian-alvarez-is-perfect-for-manchester-city/ |url-status=live}}</ref> While not being known a particularly skillful dribbler, Alvarez is described as a powerful runner. His slightly hunched running style is said to allow him to win challenges and protect the ball effectively, and there is a noted aggression to his carrying that makes him difficult to stop.<ref name=":3" /> Alvarez has typically played in a two-striker system in a team with an extremely settled style of play.<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4" />

In the 2023–24 season, Manchester City manager Pep Guardiola often used Alvarez as an attacking midfielder in the absence of Kevin De Bruyne. Alvarez's intelligent running, passing and possession has led to him thriving in this position, and he has often been lauded by pundits for successfully adapting to the requirements of the new position.<ref name=":3" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=Julian Alvarez thriving for Man City having stepped into Kevin De Bruyne void |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/12978140/julian-alvarez-thriving-for-man-city-having-stepped-into-kevin-de-bruyne-void |access-date=26 October 2023 |website=Sky Sports |language=en |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026081004/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/12978140/julian-alvarez-thriving-for-man-city-having-stepped-into-kevin-de-bruyne-void |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Hopkins |first=Oliver |date=30 September 2023 |title=Julián Álvarez: Man City's Hybrid Midfielder Who Has Stepped Up in De Bruyne's Absence |url=https://theanalyst.com/2023/09/julian-alvarez-manchester-city-stats/ |access-date=26 October 2023 |website=The Analyst |language=en |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026081004/https://theanalyst.com/2023/09/julian-alvarez-manchester-city-stats/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Murphy |first=Daniel |date=29 September 2023 |title=Julian Alvarez's best Man City role is even clearer after Newcastle blank |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-julian-alvarez-haaland-27806958 |access-date=26 October 2023 |website=Manchester Evening News |language=en |archive-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026081005/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-julian-alvarez-haaland-27806958 |url-status=live}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Alvarez holds dual [[Argentine nationality law|Argentine]]-[[Italian nationality law|Italian]] nationality, allowing him to register in La Liga as an EU player.<ref>{{cite web |date=9 August 2024 |title=Passport rule which allows Conor Gallagher and Julian Alvarez transfers to Atletico Madrid |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/passport-rule-allows-conor-gallagher-073300328.html |access-date=6 August 2025 |website=Yahoo Sports}}</ref>

Alvarez's brothers, Agustín and Rafael, are also footballers. Both played for non-league team [[Abbey Hey F.C.|Abbey Hey]] when Julián was a Manchester City player.<ref>{{cite web |title=Alvarez Bros: Premier League & Non-league |url=https://www.mancity.com/citytv/mens/Alvarez |access-date=6 August 2025 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Lee |first=Sam |date=18 December 2022 |title=Julian Alvarez is Argentina's No 9 – so why do his brothers play in England's 10th tier? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/3902874/2022/11/17/julian-alvarez-argentina-man-city/ |access-date=6 August 2025 |work=The New York Times |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> In 2025, Julián's brothers signed for Club Argentino, a team that competes in the Segunda Regional of Madrid.<ref>{{cite web |last=Team |first=Editorial |date=4 March 2025 |title=Julián Álvarez's Brothers Signed for a Club in Spain |url=https://derechadiario.com.ar/us/argentina/julian-alvarezs-brothers-also-play-in-spain |access-date=6 August 2025 |website=La Derechadiario US}}</ref>

Alvarez is in a relationship with fellow Argentine Maria Emilia Ferrero. On 22 June 2025, the couple announced that they were expecting their first child, a boy.<ref>{{cite web |date=22 June 2025 |title=Julián Álvarez confirmó que serán padres junto a su pareja Emilia Ferrero: "Estamos muy contentos" |url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes/2025/06/22/julian-alvarez-confirmo-que-seran-padres-junto-a-su-pareja-emilia-ferrero-estamos-muy-contentos/ |access-date=6 August 2025 |website=infobae |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=8 July 2025 |title=Con un penal y rodeado de familiares: el emocionante método de Julián Álvarez y Emilia Ferrero para revelar el sexo de su bebé |url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes/2025/07/08/con-un-penal-y-rodeado-de-familiares-el-emocionante-metodo-de-julian-alvarez-y-emilia-ferrero-para-revelar-el-sexo-de-su-bebe/ |access-date=6 August 2025 |website=infobae |language=es}}</ref>

Alvarez's nickname is ''"La Araña"'' (the spider) or ''"El Hombre Araña"'' ([[Spider-Man]]), reflecting his web-shooter [[goal celebration]].<ref>{{cite news |date=8 July 2022 |title=Julian Alvarez's Nickname Explained |url=https://www.si.com/fannation/soccer/futbol/news/julian-alvarez-nickname-explained-as-the-spider-joins-man-city |access-date=8 July 2022 |website=FanNation Futbol}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=13 August 2024 |title=Julian Alvarez speaks for the first time as Atletico Madrid player |url=https://m.allfootballapp.com/news/La-Liga/Julian-Alvarez-speaks-for-the-first-time-as-Atletico-Madrid-player/3456187 |access-date=6 August 2025 |website=All Football}}</ref>

